An Act relative to civil asset forfeiture data reporting.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1: Section 47 of chapter 94C of the General Laws is hereby amended by
2 striking out subparagraph (k)(1) and inserting in place thereof the following subparagraph:-
3 (k)(1) The attorney general, each district attorney and each police department for which
4 the state treasurer has established a special law enforcement trust fund pursuant to subsection (d)
5 shall file an annual report with the treasurer regarding all assets, monies and proceeds from
6 assets seized pursuant to this section and held by such fund. The report shall provide itemized
7 accounting for each seizure and forfeiture, as required by section 47B. The report shall be filed
8 not later than January 31 for the preceding calendar year and shall be a public record.
